name: UICellConfigurationState.DropState
desc: Constants that describe the cell’s drop state.

items.name: case none
items.desc: The system has not associated the cell with a drag session.

items.name: case notTargeted
items.desc: A drag session is active and can perform a drop in the cell’s container, but the cell itself isn’t the drop target.

items.name: case targeted
items.desc: The cell is the drop target for a drag session.

items.name: static func == (UICellConfigurationState.DropState, UICellConfigurationState.DropState) -> Bool
items.desc: An operator for checking whether two drop states are equal.

items.name: static func != (UICellConfigurationState.DropState, UICellConfigurationState.DropState) -> Bool
items.desc: An operator for checking whether two drop states are unequal.

items.name: func hash(into: inout Hasher)
items.desc: Hashes the essential components of the drop state by feeding them into the hasher.
